- Green Monarch.
- Damn.

975
01:04:22,733 --> 01:04:23,859
We need a Ford Granada.

976
01:04:26,487 --> 01:04:28,488
I see your Monarch...

977
01:04:29,198 --> 01:04:30,824
...I raise you Bobby Earl's...

978
01:04:30,992 --> 01:04:32,576
...Granada.

979
01:04:35,454 --> 01:04:36,830
ARMSTRONG:
They're almost identical.

980
01:04:45,464 --> 01:04:47,966
WARDEN:
I'm no friend of capital punishment...

981
01:04:48,634 --> 01:04:50,969
...but at least the letters will stop.

982
01:05:07,320 --> 01:05:09,821
WOMAN:
More of Sullivan's correspondence.

983
01:05:10,573 --> 01:05:11,781
That's the lot?

984
01:05:11,949 --> 01:05:13,742
So far.

985
01:05:32,345 --> 01:05:33,845
Warden.

986
01:05:48,027 --> 01:05:50,612
WARDEN:
"Dear Mr. and Mrs. Shriver...

987
01:05:50,780 --> 01:05:53,365
...I've been wrong
not to write to you before this...

988
01:05:53,532 --> 01:05:56,910
...but I've been real busy
getting ready to die.

989
01:05:57,119 --> 01:06:01,206
I just wanted you to know what a real...

990
01:06:02,541 --> 01:06:07,212
...sweet piece of business
your little baby was.

991
01:06:08,339 --> 01:06:13,176
Doing her was like carving up...

992
01:06:13,344 --> 01:06:14,386
...a ripe melon...

993
01:06:15,388 --> 01:06:18,682
...like picking ripe cherries
on a summer morning...

994
01:06:19,558 --> 01:06:22,185
...like plowing a scented field,
and plow her I did.

995
01:06:22,812 --> 01:06:26,982
Although, I don't imagine anything's
gonna come of that particular crop...

996
01:06:27,149 --> 01:06:29,317
...come harvest time, do you?"

997
01:06:30,903 --> 01:06:34,197
It's signed, "Your friend Blair Sullivan."

998
01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:39,035
Now...

999
01:06:39,745 --> 01:06:43,581
...he doesn't specifically say
in this letter...

1000
01:06:43,749 --> 01:06:45,875
...that he killed Joanie Shriver.

1001
01:06:47,003 --> 01:06:48,378
Does he?

1002
01:06:48,838 --> 01:06:50,005
No.

1003
01:06:51,090 --> 01:06:53,216
He said what I read.

1004
01:06:53,384 --> 01:06:57,887
That being with her was
"like carving up a ripe melon."

1005
01:07:05,396 --> 01:07:06,938
Nothing further.

1006
01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:19,117
Bobby Earl, Bobby Earl.
How does it feel being free?

1007
01:07:19,285 --> 01:07:21,286
- Uh, I'd like to thank--
- Your attorney.

1008
01:07:21,454 --> 01:07:22,829
My attorney, Mr. Lyle Morgan.

1009
01:07:22,997 --> 01:07:26,291
My grandma for never giving up hope,
and Professor Paul Armstrong.

1010
01:07:26,459 --> 01:07:28,710
If it weren't for him,
I wouldn't be standing here today.

1011
01:07:28,878 --> 01:07:30,503
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1012
01:07:34,050 --> 01:07:35,800
MAN: Bobby Earl.
WOMAN: Bobby Earl.

1013
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:39,846
MAN:
Do you have any plans to leave the city?

1014
01:07:41,140 --> 01:07:42,640
WOMAN:
Where will you reside?

1015
01:07:42,933 --> 01:07:44,017
MAN:
Bobby Earl.

1016
01:07:52,318 --> 01:07:55,737
- How are you?
LAURIE: I'm very happy for you.

1017
01:07:56,322 --> 01:07:58,364
I'm happy for both of us.

1018
01:07:59,658 --> 01:08:00,992
- Professor.
ARMSTRONG: Bobby Earl.

1019
01:08:02,244 --> 01:08:03,745
EARL:
Thank you so much.

1020
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:05,163
ARMSTRONG:
Before we go back...

1021
01:08:05,331 --> 01:08:07,373
...we'd like you to come for drinks Friday.

1022
01:08:07,541 --> 01:08:10,376
Oh, I'd love to, but I can't.
I made other plans.

1023
01:08:10,544 --> 01:08:13,088
But we'll meet again. I promise you.

1024
01:08:13,255 --> 01:08:16,049
MAN: One more shot. Got a second?
LAURIE: Congratulations.

1025
01:08:16,217 --> 01:08:17,717
- You have a safe trip.
MAN: Bobby Earl.

1026
01:08:17,885 --> 01:08:19,719
[REPORTERS CHATTERING]

1027
01:08:19,887 --> 01:08:21,971
Hey there, Mr. Ferguson.
Congratulations.

1028
01:08:22,556 --> 01:08:25,058
Congratulations.
Got them all fooled, don't you?

1029
01:08:25,226 --> 01:08:28,394
Judge, even that know-nothing
Harvard fool, huh?

1030
01:08:29,021 --> 01:08:30,313
But not me.

1031
01:08:31,690 --> 01:08:34,526
No, sir. Not Tanny Brown.

1032
01:08:34,693 --> 01:08:38,404
I'm gonna be all over you
like white on rice, boy. You hear?

1033
01:08:41,075 --> 01:08:43,576
- Come on.
- Miss Evangeline.

1034
01:08:48,165 --> 01:08:50,208
[BAND PLAYING
"I ONLY HAVE EYES FOR YOU"]

1035
01:08:56,882 --> 01:09:00,343
ARMSTRONG [SINGING]:
They all disappear

1036
01:09:00,511 --> 01:09:04,597
[HUMMING]

1037
01:09:06,183 --> 01:09:09,853
[MUMBLING LYRICS]

1038
01:09:10,729 --> 01:09:12,772
[LAURIE LAUGHING]

1039
01:09:14,525 --> 01:09:17,569
Oh, I love you.

1040
01:09:40,593 --> 01:09:42,343
LYLE:
The firm's been much more successful...

1041
01:09:42,511 --> 01:09:44,596
...than I ever dreamed it would be
when I started it.

1042
01:09:44,763 --> 01:09:48,224
- So, Lyle, are you single at all?
- I've been married for eight years.

1043
01:09:48,392 --> 01:09:50,602
Oh, good. It's time for you to fool around.

1044
01:09:50,769 --> 01:09:53,021
PHIL:
All right. Champagne, anyone?

1045
01:09:53,189 --> 01:09:57,192
- Yeah. Yes, I'd love some. Thank you, Phil.
- Thank you, Phil.

1046
01:09:57,359 --> 01:10:00,820
LIBBY: You ought to stay on a few days
and we'll make it a real vacation.

1047
01:10:00,988 --> 01:10:04,866
No, we gotta get back. I'm behind
on my caseload. Paul, you've got classes.

1048
01:10:05,034 --> 01:10:08,328
- Yep.
- Paul, I think you missed your true calling.

1049
01:10:08,495 --> 01:10:10,121
You should've been a detective.

1050
01:10:10,289 --> 01:10:13,124
No, thanks. I'm quite happy
to get out of the real world.

1051
01:10:13,292 --> 01:10:15,460
- Ha-ha-ha.
PHIL: Here we go. A little refreshment.

1052
01:10:15,628 --> 01:10:16,669
[PHONE RINGING]

1053
01:10:16,837 --> 01:10:19,964
Katie. Katie. Sweetie, get the phone.

1054
01:10:21,133 --> 01:10:23,134
Hello, hello. Hello.

1055
01:10:23,302 --> 01:10:27,263
I would like--
I would like to propose a toast.

1056
01:10:27,431 --> 01:10:29,515
To innocence revealed.

1057
01:10:29,683 --> 01:10:31,434
To death denied.

1058
01:10:31,602 --> 01:10:34,479
To the triumph of truth over appearance.

1059
01:10:34,647 --> 01:10:36,189
- Hear, hear.
- Hear, hear.

1060
01:10:36,357 --> 01:10:38,524
Telephone for you, Daddy.

1061
01:10:39,276 --> 01:10:42,195
- Don't finish it.
DELORES: What are you doing after?

1062
01:10:42,363 --> 01:10:44,906
What am I doing after the party?
I have an appointment.

1063
01:10:45,074 --> 01:10:47,492
I'm afraid, in fact,
I'm gonna have to leave now.

1064
01:10:47,660 --> 01:10:50,662
- Hello.
SULLIVAN: Well, well, well.

1065
01:10:50,829 --> 01:10:53,665
- Congratulations, professor.
- Sullivan?

1066
01:10:54,041 --> 01:10:55,375
How'd you get this number?

1067
01:10:56,877 --> 01:10:58,211
I've got all your numbers.

1068
01:10:59,380 --> 01:11:01,381
It's been a big week for you.

1069
01:11:02,841 --> 01:11:04,842
Been a big week for me too.

1070
01:11:05,010 --> 01:11:08,429
Sure you know the governor
signed my death warrant.

1071
01:11:08,597 --> 01:11:11,474
Hell, I got less time than it takes
to play a round of golf.

1072
01:11:12,434 --> 01:11:13,476
Anyways...

1073
01:11:15,354 --> 01:11:17,605
...my letter done sewed it up tight
for you.

1074
01:11:18,190 --> 01:11:20,525
We thought that might do the trick.

1075
01:11:20,693 --> 01:11:21,943
We?

1076
01:11:23,028 --> 01:11:25,655
- Who's "we"?
- I'll tell you when you get here.

1077
01:11:25,823 --> 01:11:28,616
Things worked out kind of perfect
for you, didn't it?

1078
01:11:28,784 --> 01:11:30,410
Maybe a little too perfect.

1079
01:11:31,161 --> 01:11:33,871
- You got a pen?
- Yes.

1080
01:11:35,624 --> 01:11:38,376
13 Tula Way.

1081
01:11:39,753 --> 01:11:41,379
Winterglade.

1082
01:11:42,423 --> 01:11:44,173
My folks' place.

1083
01:11:45,134 --> 01:11:47,427
I want you to call on them.

1084
01:11:48,554 --> 01:11:51,055
I want you to say goodbye for me.

1085
01:11:52,516 --> 01:11:54,475
Tell them I love them...

1086
01:11:54,643 --> 01:11:56,728
...and that they are in my prayers...

1087
01:11:58,188 --> 01:11:59,647
...and then you come to me.

1088
01:12:00,691 --> 01:12:05,069
You do that for me
and I'll tell you who "we" is.

1089
01:12:05,988 --> 01:12:08,197
You best run, Armstrong.

1090
01:12:37,436 --> 01:12:40,063
[THE ORIOLES' "CRYING IN THE CHAPEL"
PLAYING QUIETLY ON RADIO]

1091
01:12:40,230 --> 01:12:41,898
[DOORBELL RINGING]

1092
01:12:57,748 --> 01:12:58,915
Hello?

1093
01:13:06,507 --> 01:13:08,466
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1094
01:13:22,648 --> 01:13:24,148
Hello?

1095
01:13:37,037 --> 01:13:38,704
Anyone home?

1096
01:14:04,356 --> 01:14:07,775
MAN [ON RADIO]:
Ha-ha-ha. Takes me back to my youth.

1097
01:14:08,360 --> 01:14:11,863
Now, I wanna remind you all
of next Sunday's fish fry.

1098
01:14:12,322 --> 01:14:13,614
[FLOOR CREAKING]

1099
01:14:15,200 --> 01:14:18,035
And now, from the bounty of the Lord...

1100
01:14:18,203 --> 01:14:21,873
..."Amazing Grace"
on Everglade Christian Radio.

1101
01:14:22,040 --> 01:14:27,211
CHOIR [SINGING]:
Amazing Grace

1102
01:14:27,379 --> 01:14:33,009
How sweet the sound

1103
01:14:33,177 --> 01:14:34,552
[FLY BUZZING]

1104
01:14:34,720 --> 01:14:41,726
That saved a wretch like me

1105
01:14:44,813 --> 01:14:50,485
I once was lost

1106
01:14:50,652 --> 01:14:56,240
But now I'm found

1107
01:14:56,408 --> 01:14:57,825
Was blind

1108
01:14:57,993 --> 01:14:59,035
[MUSIC STOPS]

1109
01:15:33,403 --> 01:15:36,030
SULLIVAN:
"So the dead which he slew at his death...

1110
01:15:37,991 --> 01:15:40,743
...were more than they
which he slew in his life."

1111
01:15:41,620 --> 01:15:43,996
Judges 16:30.

1112
01:15:46,583 --> 01:15:48,167
I told you I had power.

1113
01:15:52,506 --> 01:15:54,215
Not this time, Armstrong.

1114
01:15:58,470 --> 01:16:00,555
So tell me...

1115
01:16:00,973 --> 01:16:02,682
...what did you see?

1116
01:16:03,642 --> 01:16:05,476
What did you hear?

1117
01:16:07,354 --> 01:16:11,566
Well, give me all the details.
Spare me nothing. Come on.

1118
01:16:13,277 --> 01:16:14,986
Come on, man, I want everything.

1119
01:16:18,490 --> 01:16:20,074
- Come on.
- No.

1120
01:16:21,577 --> 01:16:24,829
When you called me to say:

1121
01:16:24,997 --> 01:16:27,665
"We thought the letter
would do the trick"...

1122
01:16:28,166 --> 01:16:29,709
...who did you mean by "we"?

1123
01:16:33,130 --> 01:16:35,631
Come, on.
Tell me what you saw down there.

1124
01:16:35,799 --> 01:16:37,883
Tell me about my folks.
That was the deal.

1125
01:16:42,180 --> 01:16:43,306
No.

1126
01:16:52,524 --> 01:16:57,069
Okay. Why not? Okay.

1127
01:16:58,196 --> 01:17:01,282
By "we," I meant me
and the shining boy of the hour.

1128
01:17:02,868 --> 01:17:06,245
See, I pushed the buttons
to make you do the dance...

1129
01:17:06,413 --> 01:17:08,372
...to spring our boy...

1130
01:17:08,999 --> 01:17:11,250
...who, in turn, did the deed.

1131
01:17:11,585 --> 01:17:14,337
- "Did the deed"?
- You know what I'm talking about.

1132
01:17:16,173 --> 01:17:19,008
I had some unfinished business
out there.

1133
01:17:19,760 --> 01:17:22,011
I gave Bobby Earl life...

1134
01:17:23,013 --> 01:17:25,097
...so he could give me death.

1135
01:17:29,728 --> 01:17:31,103
Joanie Shriver?

1136
01:17:34,900 --> 01:17:38,569
I never had the pleasure of making
that sweet little girl's acquaintance.

1137
01:17:39,237 --> 01:17:41,906
Bobby Earl coached me a little bit
on the details.

1138
01:17:44,242 --> 01:17:47,578
All I had to do to take his crime
was tell you where the knife was...

1139
01:17:47,746 --> 01:17:49,747
...and write that letter.

1140
01:17:49,915 --> 01:17:52,917
You should see your face, Armstrong.
Ha, ha.

1141
01:17:53,085 --> 01:17:55,419
What the hell's going on up there?

1142
01:17:57,339 --> 01:18:00,216
- Why me?
- We needed us a legitimizer.

1143
01:18:00,384 --> 01:18:02,551
Who'd believe us?
We're just psychopaths.

1144
01:18:02,719 --> 01:18:05,763
- But why me?
- You were Bobby Earl's con.

1145
01:18:05,931 --> 01:18:07,348
- He had his reasons.
- Reasons?

1146
01:18:07,516 --> 01:18:09,850
- It's my turn now.
- What fucking reasons?

1147
01:18:10,018 --> 01:18:12,728
No, it's my turn now! Come on.

1148
01:18:12,896 --> 01:18:15,815
How did my folks look? Hmm?

1149
01:18:16,400 --> 01:18:18,401
How did they smell?

1150
01:18:19,736 --> 01:18:23,531
Tell me everything.
Come on. Spare me nothing.

1151
01:18:24,741 --> 01:18:26,117
Hmm?

1152
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:30,705
They said they forgive you
and they'll remember you in their prayers.

1153
01:18:31,623 --> 01:18:33,624
- No.
- Yeah.

1154
01:18:33,792 --> 01:18:35,876
I'm sure you're lying, cocksucker! No!

1155
01:18:36,253 --> 01:18:38,921
You inhuman bastard!
You cannot cheat me of this!

1156
01:18:40,090 --> 01:18:42,466
I'm screwed! Come on!

1157
01:18:43,468 --> 01:18:46,303
We played you like a tune!
It ain't over yet!

1158
01:18:46,471 --> 01:18:48,264
You got the trials of Job ahead of you!

1159
01:18:48,640 --> 01:18:52,226
The trials of Job!
The sin is pride, you motherfucker...

1160
01:18:52,394 --> 01:18:54,895
...and the messenger is revenge!

1161
01:18:57,274 --> 01:18:58,691
[DOOR SLAMS]

1162
01:18:59,401 --> 01:19:01,360
SULLIVAN [ON RECORDER]:
We played you like a tune!

1163
01:19:01,528 --> 01:19:02,778
It ain't over yet! You got to--

1164
01:19:05,782 --> 01:19:06,824
Tanny.

1165
01:19:07,117 --> 01:19:09,118
[SOBBING]

1166
01:19:15,167 --> 01:19:17,334
No!

1167
01:19:18,587 --> 01:19:20,296
[GROWLING]

1168
01:19:27,804 --> 01:19:30,306
TANNY: I told you how fragile this was.
- You're right.

1169
01:19:30,474 --> 01:19:33,058
- I said you were right.
- You know where I am?

1170
01:19:33,226 --> 01:19:36,020
I'm sitting at the Sullivan house
and I wanna tell you...

1171
01:19:36,354 --> 01:19:39,148
...it's a good thing for you
I just I put Wilcox on his tail.

1172
01:19:52,537 --> 01:19:54,830
PRIEST: "ln the name of the father, son...
- Shut up.

1173
01:19:54,998 --> 01:19:56,999
PRIEST: ...and the Holy Spirit--"
- Shut up.

1174
01:19:57,167 --> 01:19:58,417
Shut up!

1175
01:20:04,591 --> 01:20:06,884
"As governor of the state of Florida...."

1176
01:20:07,052 --> 01:20:10,638
I have a confession from Sullivan
on tape and it is evidence.

1177
01:20:10,806 --> 01:20:12,932
TANNY:
Armstrong, you're a goddamn fool.

1178
01:20:13,099 --> 01:20:16,018
First you had evidence this way,
now you got evidence that way.

1179
01:20:16,186 --> 01:20:19,980
His confession don't mean shit
unless he testifies in court.

1180
01:20:20,232 --> 01:20:24,276
Don't lecture me about confessions,
not after the way you got Bobby Earl's.

1181
01:20:25,153 --> 01:20:30,407
"--to cause the sentence of death
to be executed on Blair Sullivan."

1182
01:20:32,285 --> 01:20:33,786
[WHIMPERING]

1183
01:20:36,915 --> 01:20:39,834
TANNY:
Armstrong, you keep Sullivan alive.

1184
01:20:47,676 --> 01:20:50,427
ALL:
Our father, who art in heaven...

1185
01:20:50,595 --> 01:20:52,179
...hallowed be thy name.

1186
01:20:52,347 --> 01:20:53,597
[PHONE RINGING]

1187
01:20:53,765 --> 01:20:58,018
Thy kingdom come. Thy will be done
on earth, as it is in heaven.

1188
01:20:58,186 --> 01:21:01,188
Give us this day our daily bread.

1189
01:21:01,356 --> 01:21:03,107
And forgive us our trespasses.

1190
01:21:04,317 --> 01:21:05,818
Paul.

1191
01:21:12,617 --> 01:21:13,951
Katie, are you packed?

1192
01:21:15,287 --> 01:21:18,330
- Where are you, J.T.?
- I'm right on top of him, Tanny.

1193
01:21:18,498 --> 01:21:20,457
- Collins and 50th.
TANNY: The Eden Roc.

1194
01:21:20,625 --> 01:21:24,837
I want you to stay on his tail. Don't jump
that rabbit until I give you the green light.

1195
01:21:25,005 --> 01:21:27,047
Ten-four.

1196
01:21:27,299 --> 01:21:28,966
[RINGING]

1197
01:21:36,600 --> 01:21:37,641
[TAPE RECORDER WHIRRING]

1198
01:21:37,809 --> 01:21:40,769
SULLIVAN [ON RECORDING]: You were
Bobby Earl's con. And he had his reasons.

1199
01:21:40,937 --> 01:21:43,314
ARMSTRONG: Reason? What reasons?
SULLIVAN: It's my turn now.

1200
01:21:43,481 --> 01:21:44,690
No, it's my turn now!

1201
01:21:44,858 --> 01:21:46,400
I'm sorry, there's no answer.

1202
01:21:46,568 --> 01:21:49,111
What about messages?
Did she leave anything for me?

1203
01:21:49,279 --> 01:21:50,654
WOMAN:
Just one moment, sir.

1204
01:21:50,822 --> 01:21:53,240
SULLIVAN: We played you like a tune!
It ain't over yet!

1205
01:21:53,408 --> 01:21:57,286
You got the trials of Job ahead, mister!
The trials of Job! The sin is pride....

1206
01:21:57,454 --> 01:21:59,079
WOMAN:
Sorry, sir, no messages.

1207
01:21:59,247 --> 01:22:01,248
SULLIVAN:
--and the messenger is revenge!

1208
01:22:01,541 --> 01:22:03,000
Laurie.

1209
01:22:20,018 --> 01:22:22,436
On, no, I left him. Angus.

1210
01:22:22,604 --> 01:22:25,522
- Who?
- The teddy bear Daddy gave me. I left him.

1211
01:22:25,690 --> 01:22:28,943
- We already gave the key back.
- But we can't just leave him.

1212
01:22:29,235 --> 01:22:30,361
[SIGHS]

